  "text": "K111R and K111R/K112R mutant proteins were expressed at reduced levels. This likely reflects their lack of transcriptional activity; we routinely observe that E2 stimulates its own transcription in transient assays [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . However, titration of increasing amounts of the K111R mutant did not result in increased activation, indicating that the deficiency is not due to a dosage effect (Fig. 4E) . The reduction of transcriptional activity with K111 mutation to arginine suggests that acetylation of this residue is necessary for transcriptional activation.",
